Sentencas: A stable, easily sintered perovskite oxide BaCe0.5Zr0.3Y0.16Zn0.04O3-delta (BCZYZ) as electrolyte for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells with Ba0.5Sr0.5Zn0.2Fe0.8O3-delta-BaCe0.5Zr0.3Y0.16Zn0.04O3-delta (BSZF-BCZYZ) composite cathode was investigated.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Zn0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-BaCe0.5Zr0.3Y0.16Zn0.04O3-δ composite cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thin proton-conducting BCZYZ electrolyte was prepared over porous anode substrate composed of NiO-BCZYZ by the one-step dry-pressing/co-firing method.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Zn0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-BaCe0.5Zr0.3Y0.16Zn0.04O3-δ composite cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A laboratory-sized tri-layer cell of NiO-BCZYZ//BCZYZ (similar to 21 mu m)/BSZF-BCZYZ (similar to 32 mu m) was operated from 550 to 700 degrees C with humidified hydrogen (similar to 3% H2O) as fuel and the static air as oxidant.
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Zn0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-BaCe0.5Zr0.3Y0.16Zn0.04O3-δ composite cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The BCZYZ perovskite electrolyte synthesized by a modified Pechini process was completely dense after sintered at 1250 degrees C for 5 h, lower than that without Znic dopant about 150 degrees C. An open-circuit potential of 1.007 V, a maximum power density of 387 mWcm(-2), and a low polarization resistance of the electrodes of 0.11 Omega cm(2) were achieved at 700 degrees C. (C) 2009
Titulo: Ba0.5Sr0.5Zn0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-BaCe0.5Zr0.3Y0.16Zn0.04O3-δ composite cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
